    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's not just a mistake though. it's more like... i'm just a constant weight on them. everything i do just makes their lives harder. i look at them and i just feel so guilty that they even have to deal with me. it feels like the only way they'd actually be happy is if i wasn't constantly there casting this shadow over everything.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is incredibly painful to feel this way, but please remember that guilt often fuels hopelessness rather than reality. Children often suffer most not from a parent's flaws or pain, but from feeling compelled to suffer *along* with them or trying to \"fix\" emotions they cannot yet understand. Taking a deep breath to hold space for yourself in grief or anger can sometimes bring healing to their hearts over the long term. You deserve self-compassion because hurting yourself hurts them worse in the end.",
